Expressions

Construct made up of variables, operators, and method invocations. This is
constructed according to the syntax of the language, that evaluates to a single
value. Core component of statements. Order of operations governs which
order operators are evaluated.

Statements

* Roughly equivalent to sentences in natural languages.
* Forms a complete unit of execution.
* Expression Statements: Expressions can be made into statements by terminating
    the expression with a semicolon (;).
* Declaration Statements: Declares a variable.
* Control Flow Statements: Regulate the order in which statements get executed.

Blocks

A group of zero or more statements between balanced braces and can be used
anywhere a single statement is allowed.